1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,000
Dealer selection is the first execution decision.

2
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:12,000
BondWorks scores counterparties before an RFQ is sent.

3
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:19,000
A trader sends a five-million-dollar RFQ for a ten-year Treasury.

4
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:28,000
Quotes arrive with price, yield, spread, size, latency, and status.

5
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:34,000
Choosing a non-best quote requires a best-execution rationale.

6
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:43,000
The fill is compared against best quote, cover price, mid, last print, and tape VWAP.

7
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:51,000
The audit trail records every lifecycle event from RFQ creation to analytics.

8
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:58,000
Underneath is Spring Boot, Postgres, Redis, Redpanda, WebSockets, and a Python strategy API.

9
00:00:58,000 --> 00:01:00,000
BondWorks Lite: execution intelligence for electronic bond markets.
